-- SodaStream Jumps to Three-Month High in New York on Europe Sales
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   H a r v e y
-- 2012-06-27T19:29:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/sodastream-jumps-to-three-month-high-in-new-york-on-europe-sales.html
SodaStream International Ltd. (SODA)  rose
to the highest level in three months in  New York  after the
Israeli maker of soda machines said its European business
remains “healthy.”  Shares of the Airport City, Israel-based company jumped 4.9
percent to $39.50 by 3:24 p.m. in New York, the highest level
since March 2. The shares are headed for a 17 percent advance
this quarter, the biggest three-month gain in 2012.  SodaStream pared a loss of as much as 1.2 percent after
Yonah Lloyd, executive director of corporate development, spoke
at an Oppenheimer & Co. consumer conference today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Harvey in New York at 
